ğŸ› ï¸ Step 3: Create Your First Jenkins Job
ğŸ”¹ 1ï¸âƒ£ Create a Basic Freestyle Job
Go to Jenkins Dashboard â†’ New Item
Enter a Job Name (e.g., First-Jenkins-Job)
Select Freestyle Project â†’ Click OK
Scroll down to Build Steps, select "Execute Shell"
Add the following script:
echo "Hello, Jenkins! This is my first job."
Click Save & Build Now

âœ… Verify Output:
Go to Build History â†’ Console Output
